Police in Ogun State have arrested a member of an armed robbery syndicate allegedly terrorising motorists plying the Sagamu-Benin Expressway. The suspect, Michael Edeh, was arrested on Saturday for allegedly hijacking a truck loaded with cocoa. About five other accomplices, who also belong to the syndicate, fled on sighting operatives of the police patrol team attached to Obalende Division in Ijebu-Ode. A statement Sunday by the state Police Public Relations Officer, Abimbola Oyeyemi, disclosed that armed men numbering about six attacked a truck with registration number Lagos KTU 286 SQ loaded with 480 bags of cocoa at a point along the Sagamu-Ijebu Ode Expressway on Saturday.  Oyeyemi, a Deputy Superintendent of Police, stated that the suspects tied the truck driver on both hands and legs and dumped him in the bush.